//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

This is my vim config. 

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

All the files in this repository are supposed to end up in the 
directory "~/.vim/". 

The file "~/.vimrc" should only contain the following line:

runtime vimrc 

The file "~/.vim/vimrc" will then be the actual "~/.vimrc".

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

To make SyncTex work, add the following line to the file "~/.bashrc":

alias vim='vim --servername VIM'

If you are using Okular as the PDF viewer, then in Okular you need to go to "Settings > Configure Okular > Editor" and there you have to choose "Custom Text Editor" as editor and then enter the following text under "Command": "gvim --remote-silent %f -c %l"

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

To make YouCompleteMe work, part of the installation has to be done manually.

Auto completion for C/C++ also requires the generation of a
compilation database for a specific project. If using CMake,
this compilation database can be generated by adding the following 
line to "CMakeLists.txt":
 
set(CMAKE_EXPORT_COMPILE_COMMANDS ON)

The generated file (which will be in the build folder where CMake 
has been called) can then be symlinked to the root of the project.

Further details are explained in the YouCompleteMe documentation.

//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
